American Axle & Manufacturing Holdings Inc

Rai Favela |
Domingo, Julio 16, 2017







Deutsche Bank AG reissued a "buy" rating and set a $22.00 target price (down previously from $24.00) on shares of American Axle & Manufacturing Holdings in a research report on Thursday, June 22nd. The stock spiked 3.58% last month and is up 11.4 this year.By historical standards, American Axle & Manufacturing Holdings, Inc. Where the relative strength index (RSI) is a technical momentum indicator that compares the magnitude of recent gains to recent losses in an attempt to determine excess buying & selling conditions of an asset, it is one of the most popular technical indicators, computed on the basis of the speed and direction of a stock's price movement.
Guggenheim started coverage with an initial rating of "Buy". J P Morgan Chase & Co reiterated an "overweight" rating on shares of American Axle & Manufacturing Holdings in a report on Monday, May 15th. Its minimum price target estimates has been figured out at $11 while the maximum price target forecast is established at $24. Geode Capital Management LLC's holdings in American Axle & Manufacturing Holdings were worth $19,689,000 as of its most recent filing with the SEC. Also, the current price highlights a discount of 43.11% to analysts' high consensus price target.02/13/2017 - American Axle & Manufacturing Holdings, Inc. had its " rating reiterated by analysts at FBR Capital Markets. The lowest price the stock reached in the last trading day was $16.29 and compares with the $12.61 52-week low.On November 16 the company was downgraded from " to "Sector Weight" by KeyBanc. Comerica Bank raised its stake in American Axle & Manufacturing Holdings by 5.5% in the fourth quarter. (NYSE:AXL) was upgraded by BidaskClub from a "strong sell" rating to a "sell" rating in a research note issued on Wednesday, June 14th. American Axle & Manufacturing Holdings, Inc. Zacks Investment Research lowered shares of American Axle & Manufacturing Holdings from a "hold" rating to a "strong sell" rating in a report on Monday.TRADEMARK VIOLATION NOTICE: "American Axle & Manufacturing Holdings, Inc".08/12/2015 - American Axle & Manufacturing Holdings, Inc. had its " rating reiterated by analysts at Susquehanna. Its last month's stock price volatility remained 2.62% which for the week approaches 2.98%.American Axle & Manufacturing Holdings, Inc. has a 50 day moving average of 15.60 and a 200 day moving average of 18.18. It has a market cap of $1.87 Billion. State of Alaska Department of Revenue increased its position in shares of American Axle & Manufacturing Holdings by 2.1% in the first quarter.American Axle & Manufacturing Holdings, Inc.American Axle & Manufacturing Holdings, Inc (AAM) manufactures, engineers, designs and validates driveline and drivetrain systems and related components and chassis modules for light trucks, sport utility vehicles, crossover vehicles, passenger cars and commercial vehicles. Its driveline and drivetrain systems include components that transfer power from the transmission and deliver it to the drive wheels. Its driveline, drivetrain and related products include axles, driveheads, chassis modules, driveshafts, power transfer units, transfer cases, chassis and steering components, transmission parts, electric drive systems and metal-formed products. As of April 6, 2017, it operated in 17 countries and had approximately 90 manufacturing, engineering and business office facilities around the world. News & Ratings Via Email - Enter your email address below to receive a concise daily summary of the latest news and analysts' ratings for American Axle & Manufacturing Holdings, Inc. with MarketBeat.com's FREE daily email newsletter.




