Supplemental Information 1




Company Profile




■URLhttp://www.aam.com
■AddressOne Dauch Drive, Detroit, MI 48211-1198, USA




Business Overview


-The Company manufactures driveline and drivetrain systems and their related components and chassis modules for light trucks, SUVs, passenger cars, crossover vehicles, and commercial vehicles.
Major Customers
 -The Company is the principal supplier of driveline components to GM for its fullsize rear-wheel drive (RWD) light trucks and SUVs manufactured in North America, supplying substantially all of GM's rear axle, four-wheel drive, and all-wheel drive (4WD/AWD) axles for these vehicle platforms. The Company is also the sole-source supplier to GM for certain axles and other driveline products for the life of each GM vehicle program covered by Life Program Contracts and Long Term Program Contracts (LPCs). -The Company is the principal supplier of driveline system products to FCA US LLC for heavy-duty Ram full-size pickup trucks and its derivatives, the AWD Jeep Cherokee, the AWD Chrysler 200, and a passenger car driveshaft program.-In recent years, the Company is looking to diversify its customer base and reduce its dependence on GM. In the fiscal year ended December 31, 2009, GM accounted for approximately 77% of the Company's net sales. During the fiscal year ended December 31, 2015, sales to GM accounted for approximately 66% of the Company's net sales. The Company hopes to reduce the percentage of total sales made to GM below 50% by 2020.-In addition, sales to customers other than GM during the fiscal year ended December 31, 2015 increased 9.8% over the previous year to USD 1,317.1 million, setting a new record for the Company.
 
